[
  "Ali Ghodsi is cofounder and CEO of data software startup Databricks, which was valued by investors at $28 billion in early 2021.",
  "Besides blue-chip investors like Coatue and Tiger Global, Databricks is also backed by cloud giants Amazon, Google, Microsoft and Salesforce.",
  "After a stint in academia, Ghodsi cofounded Databricks with a group of UC Berkeley peers, including the creators of analytics engine Apache Spark.",
  "Databricks is built on top of Spark, and serves as, in Ghodsi's words, a \"data lake house\" that helps companies store and utilize their data.",
  "Firms like Comcast, Credit Suisse and T-Mobile use Databricks to layer business intelligence and machine learning tools on top of their data."
]